img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/d44bc5c0-3b42-11ee-9bfb-3a5a493c7cee" style="height:924px;width:1600px;" alt="A white car against a white background with pricing information for Tesla Model S." data-uuid="99a1b516-cf14-3341-96f0-614fba5ffea4"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">特斯拉</div></figure><p>As <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://electrek.co/2023/08/14/tesla-launches-model-s-x-with-standard-range/"><em>Electrek</em></a> noted when it noticed the presence of Standard Range vehicles on Tesla&#39;s website, it&#39;s not clear if the automaker is making battery packs especially for these releases or if it&#39;s merely software-locking packs for its EVs with longer ranges. If it&#39;s the latter, then Tesla might give customers the opportunity to unlock longer ranges in the future if they&#39;re willing to pay for it. The new Standard Range EVs are available for the aforementioned prices in Pearl White with an all-black interior, along with standard wheels and steering wheel. Buyers will have to pay extra for other colors, customizations, and, of course, for Tesla&#39;s Enhanced Autopilot ($6,000) and Full Self-Driving Capability ($15,000) features.</p><p> Tesla is giving current customers the <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tesla-offers-customers-one-time-full-self-driving-transfer-until-september-30th-150004266.html">option to transfer Full Self-Driving</a> to a newly purchased vehicle for free at the moment. That said, they can only take advantage of this one-time amnesty if they take delivery of a new EV between July 20th and September 30th, 2023. Seeing as the new Standard Range vehicles could be delivered after September, buyers should be aware that they might have to pay for FSD again even if they already have it in their current Tesla EV.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/tesla-begins-selling-cheaper-model-s-and-model-x-variants-with-shorter-ranges-082045956.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/tesla-begins-selling-cheaper-model-s-and-model-x-variants-with-shorter-ranges-082045956.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> add1e64c-f38b-4707-bf3b-ee2d2107edc9</guid><dc:creator>玛丽埃拉·穆恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 15 Aug 2023 08:20:45 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1692087634</ingested><modified> 2023-08-15T08:20:39+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Automotive Industry]]></category><category><![CDATA[Autos]]></category><category><![CDATA[Transportation]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="3696" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-11/9f244360-704d-11ed-bfbf-135a5110df30" width="5483"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3696" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-11/9f244360-704d-11ed-bfbf-135a5110df30" width="5483"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Future Publishing via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[HANGZHOU, CHINA - NOVEMBER 27, 2022 - Customers walk past a Tesla store in Hangzhou, Zhejiang province, China, Nov 27, 2022. [Photo/IC] Tesla Inc has recalled 80,561 imported Model S and Model X electric cars and some imported and domestically produced Model 3 electric cars, the State Administration for Market Regulation announced. (Photo credit should read CFOTO/Future Publishing via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Tesla Recalls More than 80000 Cars]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[An Iowa school district is using AI to ban books]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>当然，没过多久，人工智能的另一只鞋就掉下来了，因为新兴技术已经被用来<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/chatgpt-scams-are-the-new-crypto-scams-meta-warns-120006510.html">进行信任诈骗</a>并<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/cnet-gets-caught-playing-ai-mad-libs-with-its-financial-news-coverage-001026432.html">生成垃圾内容</a>。我们现在可以在该列表中添加审查制度，因为《 <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://globegazette.com/news/local/book-ban-implemented-in-mason-city-school-library/article_1e45064a-386a-11ee-82f7-c3e222c4871a.html"><em>环球公报》</em>报道称</a><a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.masoncityschools.org/index.php/board-of-education">，爱荷华州梅森市的学校董事会</a>已开始利用人工智能技术，在 2023/24 学年之前从该地区的图书馆中制定可能被禁止的书籍清单。</p><p> 5 月，共和党控制的州立法机构通过了<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/publications/LGE/90/SF496.pdf">参议院文件 496</a> (SF 496)，州长 Kim Reynolds 随后签署了该文件，对该州的教育课程进行了彻底的修改。具体来说，它限制了学校图书馆和教室可以提供的书籍，要求书名“适合年龄”并且没有“性行为的描述或视觉描绘”，根据<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.legis.iowa.gov/legislation/BillBook?ga=90&amp;ba=SF496">爱荷华州法典 702.17</a> 。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>但确保该地区档案馆中的每一本书都遵守这些新规则很快就会变成一项艰巨的任务。梅森城社区学区课程和教学助理总监布里吉特·埃克斯曼 (Bridgette Exman) 在一份声明中表示：“我们的教室和学校图书馆拥有大量藏书，包括购买、捐赠和发现的文本。” “阅读每一本书并过滤这些新要求是根本不可行的。”</p><p>因此，梅森市学区正在引入人工智能来解析可疑文本，以查找被禁止的想法和描述，因为人类审阅者无法自行涵盖太多标题。根据该学区的说法，首先根据之前是否有过性内容投诉，从“多个来源”拼凑出一份“总清单”。然后，“人工智能软件”会扫描该列表中的书籍，该软件会告诉国家审查人员书中是否确实存在对性的描述。</p><p> “坦率地说，我们有更重要的事情要做，而不是花大量时间试图找出如何保护孩子们免受书籍侵害，”埃克斯曼通过电子邮件告诉<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.popsci.com/technology/iowa-chatgpt-book-ban/"><em>PopSci</em></a> 。 “与此同时，我们确实有遵守法律的法律和道德义务。我们的目标确实是一个可防御的过程。”</p><p>到目前为止，人工智能已标记 19 本书为删除。它们如下：</p><ul><li><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9LaWxsaW5nLUdyaWZmaW4tTG9pcy1EdW5jYW4tVGhyaWxsZXJzL2RwLzAzMTYwOTkwMDc_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tMXRkLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI3OWU1NDg4Ny1hNjZmLTRkYTUtOTAyYy0xMDYyOTA1ODgyZjgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAeTuv26ogDgVhQZdee1a1M_LfUhBlO8cKZxwJIfhXM9L&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FKilling-Griffin-Lois-Duncan-Thrillers%2Fdp%2F0316099007" class="rapid-with-clickid"><em>杀死格里芬先生</em></a>路易斯·邓肯</p></li><li><p>由帕特里夏·麦考密克<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfgRkUKBRwYuTd1cZbDA25amKNP5UjkMnSn1NpUFz2ka&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSOLD-Patricia-McCormick%2Fdp%2F0786851724" class="rapid-with-clickid"><em>出售</em></a></p></li><li><p>莎拉·J·马斯的<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAXcbxuMnVKPyTgZUtDNtILgFYWa-EJnxkAbdllAYM9LR&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FCourt-Thorns-Roses-Sarah-Maas%2Fdp%2F1635575567" class="rapid-with-clickid"><em>《迷雾与愤怒的法庭</em></a>》（系列）</p></li><li><p>蒂芙尼·杰克逊 (Tiffany D. Jackson) 的<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.c